## What I Worked On Today

The HIPAA Security Rule (45 CFR Part 164, Subpart C) organizes safeguards into three categories: administrative safeguards (§164.308), physical safeguards (§164.310), and technical safeguards (§164.312). Required specifications are mandatory; addressable specifications require implementation or documented rationale for alternatives. Today I work through the technical safeguards in full depth and the most critical administrative safeguards, with the evidence chain for each.

